contentrichtext.text: '''IUP''' may refer to: * [[Indiana University of Pennsylvania]], the largest of the state-owned universities in the Pennsylvania State System of Higher Education * [[IUP Crimson Hawks]], the intercollegiate athletic program of the above school * [[IUP Portfolio]], a Swedish short for individual development plan * [[IUP (software)]], a computer software that provides a portable, scriptable toolkit for GUI building. * [[Industrial Union Party]] * [[Interconnect User Part]], UK specific SS7 protocol * [[Inter-University Program for Chinese Language Study]] at [[Tsinghua University]] * Intrauterine [[Pregnancy]], the normal location for a pregnancy to occur * [[Intrinsically unstructured protein]] {{disambig}}
